Hi @tomaszn!

From looking at the CSV specification ([RFC 4180](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4180)), I don't see any standard defined for adding a caption or title to CSV data.

I just pushed an update to the output widget which allows you to use the [`output_callback` function](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-output.html#output_callback) to return a modified string instead of just a boolean. Use it like this ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/abkNM/7487/)):

```js
output_callback :  function(config, data)  {
	return config.$table.children('caption').text() + '\n' + data;
}
```

With this change you can do whatever you want to the data.

