Hi!
I'm not very fond of Flask-restful error handling, motly because text based approch oes not support inheritance.

In Flask-RESTPlus, the prefered approcha is using the `@api.errorhandler` decorator which is type-based and support inheritance.

A simple example with Flask-Principal PermissionDenied:
```python
@api.errorhandler(PermissionDenied)
def handle_permission_denied(error):
    message = 'You do not have the required permission to perform this action.'
    return {
        'message': message
    }, 403
```

You can return whatever you want or need, with the HTTP status code you want.

