@piiswrong 
> What exactly is the difference between this and updater?

It's an Updater for the *gradients*, not the parameters themselves. Another fitting name would be GradientUpdater. The other main difference is that it receives information about the source of the pushed gradient. The default `+=` rule doesn't work for several, more interesting, use cases.

